  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study hopes to determine if thromboelastography-derived functional fibrinogen (TEG-FF)
      levels on cardiopulmary bypass during cardiac surgery can provide information on coagulation
      status sooner, allowing for anticipation of post-bypass bleeding and transfusion requirements
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
